{l s='Under the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), people are entitled to data portability, i.e. the transferability of personal data.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='In the GDPR (article 20) this is called the right to data portability.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='It means that people have the right to receive the personal information an organization has of them. This has to be provided in a machine readable format.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='You must provide all personal data that your customers have provided to you. But you have to take this seriously.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='This not only concerns data that customers have actively and consciously provided to you, such as the account details (e-mail address, username, age etc.) they have entered through an online form.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='It also concerns the information that customers have provided to you by using your service or device.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='When requesting data portability, you do not have to provide any derived data, which means, data that you generated yourself. For example, a data analysis.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='Inform people about the right to data portablilty. People can send a request to export their personal data from the right to data portability account block.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='You can eighter automate this process, or you can give your approval first.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='The module will generate a CSV file with all of the personal data which has been collected on your shop.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='This module complies with other modules which have been made GDPR compliant.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
